cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.LG

The paper deals with wireless video streaming for VR applications, which involves networking (cs.NI) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects. The proposed scheme uses deep learning (cs.CV) and game theory (cs.GT) to optimize the scheduling and content quality adaptation. The paper also mentions the use of the Lyapunov framework (cs.DC) to model the problem and the clustering of users based on their predicted FoV similarity and location (cs.LG).
